<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-57-0645 </DOCNO><TEXT>Miniature silicon photodiodes were tested for utilization in radiotherapy.Their use in the treatment of carcinoma laryngis is described. The actuallygiven dose was monitored during irradiation. Treatment plan or the settingup of the entrance fields was modified according to the response of thediode. This method seems to be useful for checking both the treatmentplan and appropriate setting up of the patients in treatment position.(author) 3 refs.; 2 figs.</TEXT></DOC>